  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: b195a4e9a62f7ca41901229184c2c4fe, type: 3}
  m_Name: SkeletonDialogue
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::DialogueModel
  description: This scriptable object contains all the needed info for the dialogue
    to play. The conversation list hold an object collection which contains the character
    information that tells the line and the line string.
  Conversation:
  - Line: "[interact] Careful where you step, Keeper! I\u2019ve just spent the morning
      polishing my kneecaps with moonlight and old silk."
    CharacterInfo: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 2287ce382842e624180a2b51ba0a2e56, type: 2}
  - Line: "[continue] They look lovely, Barnaby, but you\u2019ve got a stray dandelion
      stuck in your ribs again. Hold still while I reach in. "
    CharacterInfo: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 5c997e2e5a0959546b5cd1b6b04fc4d9, type: 2}
  - Line: '[skip] Oh! Keep it there. It tickles, and frankly, I haven''t felt a tickle
      since the late 1700s.'
    CharacterInfo: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 2287ce382842e624180a2b51ba0a2e56, type: 2}
